Pasta alla Martina -  fresh tomato saut√©ed with garlic, oil and white wine, fresh asparagus, peas, shrimp and basil. Tossed together with pappardelle. Felicity thinks it would have been better with spaghetti.

Happy as a clam. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚Ä¢ 1 pound spaghetti ‚†Ä
‚Ä¢ 1 pound of clams (smaller the better)‚†Ä
‚Ä¢ handful of chopped parsley‚†Ä
‚Ä¢ 2 cloves of garlic roughly chopped ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
**serves 4 OR me and my wife‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Put your clams in a bowl of very salty water for 20 minutes to purge them of any dirt. Discard any that are open before cooking. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Put the pasta on to boil in salted water ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Place a large frying pan on a medium to high heat add a glug of extra virgin Olive oil.  throw in your garlic and cook for one minute until soft (move garlic around the pan to prevent it from burning)‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Add your clams to the frying pan and turn heat to high. Cook until all or nearly all are open. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Add your parsley ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Drain pasta reserving one cup of pasta water ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Add cooked pasta to the frying pan with half of the reserved pasta water and toss. (Add more water if it looks too dry)‚†Ä
‚†Ä
- Add salt and a splash of extra virgin olive oil to taste.
